<TITLE>AMASS: Algorithm for MSI Analysis by Semi-supervised Segmentation</TITLE>
<LINK rel="stylesheet" href="mystyles.css">
</HEAD>

<BODY>

<script src="navigation.js" type="text/javascript"> </script>

<div class="indent1">
<P>
      AMASS is a series of tools written in C++ that allows you to segment your mass spectrometry imaging dataset into regions with similar molecular signatures. The software allows for user input at each step of the process and returns the regions as well as the associated molecular signatures. It is composed of two dynamic libraries and a series of executables using the libraries as a base.
</P>
<p>
      Additionally, we provide a Graphical User Interface (GUI) to allow easy access to the libraries. The GUI is written in python using the TKInter interface.
</p>
<p>
     The main software binaries and source code are available for <A href="my_account.php">download</A>. Please see the instructions on <A HREF="usage.html#install">installation</A> and <A HREF="usage.html#usage">usage</A>.
</P>
<P>
      We also provide a gimp plugin for creating masks which is available <a HREF="gimp_plugin.html">here</a>.
</P>

<BR> <BR>

<P>
  You can find more details on this work in the following manuscripts.
</p>
<ul>
  <li>
  Bruand J, Alexandrov T, Sistla S, Wisztorski M, Mériaux C, Becker M, Salzet M, Fournier I, 
  Macagno E, Bafna V. AMASS: Algorithm for MSI Analysis by Semi-supervised Segmentation. 
  <i>J Proteome Res</i> 10(10):4734-43. 
  <A href="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/21800894">PMID:21800894</A>.
  <A href="http://pubs.acs.org/doi/abs/10.1021/pr2005378">ACS link</A>.
  </li>
  <li>
  Bruand J, Sistla S, Mériaux C, Dorrestein PC, Gaasterland T, Ghassemian M, Wisztorski M, 
  Fournier I, Salzet M, Macagno E, Bafna V. 2011. Automated querying and identification of 
  novel peptides using MALDI mass spectrometric imaging.
  <i>J Proteome Res</i> 10(4):1915-28. 
  <A href="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/21332220">PMID:21332220</A>.
  <A href="http://pubs.acs.org/doi/abs/10.1021/pr101159e">ACS link</A>.
  </li>
</ul>


